oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Normal Uterine Physiology and Involution
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Thatcher, William W.
Guilbault, Louis A.
Drost, Maarten
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Uterine Physiology
postpartum uterus
calving interval
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A 12 to a 13 month calving interval should be the goal of dairymen and veterinary practitioners who want tomaximize both breeding and milk production efficiency. The objective of this presentation is to describespecifically the normal physiology and involution of thepostpartum uterus in dairy cows.
